.TH CODEX-HISTORY 1 "May 2026" "codex-history-viewer 0.1.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
codex-history \- browse codex-cli session history in a terminal interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B codex-history
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B codex-history
opens a two-pane terminal viewer for Codex CLI sessions stored under
.IR ~/.codex/sessions .
It supports text search, syntax-highlighted change cards, and optional tool
activity display.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-dir " " \fIPATH\fR
Read sessions from
.IR PATH .
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-search " " \fITEXT\fR
Filter sessions by matching text.
.TP
.BR \-\-session " " \fIID\fR
Select a session by identifier or filename fragment.
.TP
.B \-\-list
List matching dialogs without opening the interactive interface.
.TP
.B \-\-plain
Print one selected dialog without opening the interactive interface.
.TP
.B \-\-tools
Include tool activity in plain output or show it on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Disable ANSI color output.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show command help.
.SH INTERACTIVE KEYS
.TP
.B /
Search sessions and conversation text.
.TP
.B n / N
Navigate to the next or previous search match.
.TP
.B t
Show or hide tool activity.
.TP
.B r
Copy a
.B codex resume
command for the selected session.
.TP
.B q
Quit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.codex/sessions
Default Codex CLI session storage directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR codex (1)
